11// This file contains classes that implement RtpSenderInterface.
12// An RtpSender associates a MediaStreamTrackInterface with an underlying
13// transport (provided by AudioProviderInterface/VideoProviderInterface)

49// Internal interface used by PeerConnection.
50class RtpSenderInternal : public RtpSenderInterface {
51 public:
52 // Sets the underlying MediaEngine channel associated with this RtpSender.
53 // A VoiceMediaChannel should be used for audio RtpSenders and
54 // a VideoMediaChannel should be used for video RtpSenders.
55 // Must call SetMediaChannel(nullptr) before the media channel is destroyed.
56 virtual void SetMediaChannel(cricket::MediaChannel* media_channel) = 0;
57
58 // Used to set the SSRC of the sender, once a local description has been set.
59 // If |ssrc| is 0, this indiates that the sender should disconnect from the
60 // underlying transport (this occurs if the sender isn't seen in a local
61 // description).
62 virtual void SetSsrc(uint32_t ssrc) = 0;
63
64 virtual void set_stream_ids(const std::vector<std::string>& stream_ids) = 0;
65 virtual void set_init_send_encodings(
66 const std::vector<RtpEncodingParameters>& init_send_encodings) = 0;
67 virtual void set_transport(
68 rtc::scoped_refptr<DtlsTransportInterface> dtls_transport) = 0;
69
70 virtual void Stop() = 0;
71
72 // |GetParameters| and |SetParameters| operate with a transactional model.
73 // Allow access to get/set parameters without invalidating transaction id.
74 virtual RtpParameters GetParametersInternal() const = 0;
75 virtual RTCError SetParametersInternal(const RtpParameters& parameters) = 0;
76
77 // Returns an ID that changes every time SetTrack() is called, but
78 // otherwise remains constant. Used to generate IDs for stats.
79 // The special value zero means that no track is attached.
80 virtual int AttachmentId() const = 0;
81
82 // Disables the layers identified by the specified RIDs.
83 // If the specified list is empty, this is a no-op.
84 virtual RTCError DisableEncodingLayers(
85 const std::vector<std::string>& rid) = 0;
86
87 virtual void SetTransceiverAsStopped() = 0;
88};
89
90// Shared implementation for RtpSenderInternal interface.
91class RtpSenderBase : public RtpSenderInternal, public ObserverInterface {
92 public:
93 class SetStreamsObserver {
94 public:
95 virtual ~SetStreamsObserver() = default;
96 virtual void OnSetStreams() = 0;
97 };
98
99 // Sets the underlying MediaEngine channel associated with this RtpSender.
100 // A VoiceMediaChannel should be used for audio RtpSenders and
101 // a VideoMediaChannel should be used for video RtpSenders.
102 // Must call SetMediaChannel(nullptr) before the media channel is destroyed.
103 void SetMediaChannel(cricket::MediaChannel* media_channel) override;
104
105 bool SetTrack(MediaStreamTrackInterface* track) override;
106 rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamTrackInterface> track() const override {
107 return track_;
108 }
109
110 RtpParameters GetParameters() const override;
111 RTCError SetParameters(const RtpParameters& parameters) override;
112
113 // |GetParameters| and |SetParameters| operate with a transactional model.
114 // Allow access to get/set parameters without invalidating transaction id.
115 RtpParameters GetParametersInternal() const override;
116 RTCError SetParametersInternal(const RtpParameters& parameters) override;
117
118 // Used to set the SSRC of the sender, once a local description has been set.
119 // If |ssrc| is 0, this indiates that the sender should disconnect from the
120 // underlying transport (this occurs if the sender isn't seen in a local
121 // description).
122 void SetSsrc(uint32_t ssrc) override;
123 uint32_t ssrc() const override { return ssrc_; }
124
125 std::vector<std::string> stream_ids() const override { return stream_ids_; }
126 void set_stream_ids(const std::vector<std::string>& stream_ids) override {
127 stream_ids_ = stream_ids;
128 }
129 void SetStreams(const std::vector<std::string>& stream_ids) override;
130
131 std::string id() const override { return id_; }
132
133 void set_init_send_encodings(
134 const std::vector<RtpEncodingParameters>& init_send_encodings) override {
135 init_parameters_.encodings = init_send_encodings;
136 }
137 std::vector<RtpEncodingParameters> init_send_encodings() const override {
138 return init_parameters_.encodings;
139 }
140
141 void set_transport(
142 rtc::scoped_refptr<DtlsTransportInterface> dtls_transport) override {
143 dtls_transport_ = dtls_transport;
144 }
145 rtc::scoped_refptr<DtlsTransportInterface> dtls_transport() const override {
146 return dtls_transport_;
147 }
148
149 void SetFrameEncryptor(
150 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameEncryptorInterface> frame_encryptor) override;
151
152 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameEncryptorInterface> GetFrameEncryptor()
153 const override {
154 return frame_encryptor_;
155 }
156
157 void Stop() override;
158
159 // Returns an ID that changes every time SetTrack() is called, but
160 // otherwise remains constant. Used to generate IDs for stats.
161 // The special value zero means that no track is attached.
162 int AttachmentId() const override { return attachment_id_; }
163
164 // Disables the layers identified by the specified RIDs.
165 // If the specified list is empty, this is a no-op.
166 RTCError DisableEncodingLayers(const std::vector<std::string>& rid) override;
167
168 void SetEncoderToPacketizerFrameTransformer(
169 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer) override;
170
171 void SetTransceiverAsStopped() override { is_transceiver_stopped_ = true; }
172
173 protected:
174 // If |set_streams_observer| is not null, it is invoked when SetStreams()
175 // is called. |set_streams_observer| is not owned by this object. If not
176 // null, it must be valid at least until this sender becomes stopped.
177 RtpSenderBase(rtc::Thread* worker_thread,
178 const std::string& id,
179 SetStreamsObserver* set_streams_observer);
180 // TODO(nisse): Since SSRC == 0 is technically valid, figure out
181 // some other way to test if we have a valid SSRC.
182 bool can_send_track() const { return track_ && ssrc_; }
183
184 virtual std::string track_kind() const = 0;
185
186 // Enable sending on the media channel.
187 virtual void SetSend() = 0;
188 // Disable sending on the media channel.
189 virtual void ClearSend() = 0;
190
191 // Template method pattern to allow subclasses to add custom behavior for
192 // when tracks are attached, detached, and for adding tracks to statistics.
193 virtual void AttachTrack() {}
194 virtual void DetachTrack() {}
195 virtual void AddTrackToStats() {}
196 virtual void RemoveTrackFromStats() {}
197
198 rtc::Thread* worker_thread_;
199 uint32_t ssrc_ = 0;
200 bool stopped_ = false;
201 bool is_transceiver_stopped_ = false;
202 int attachment_id_ = 0;
203 const std::string id_;
204
205 std::vector<std::string> stream_ids_;
206 RtpParameters init_parameters_;
207
208 cricket::MediaChannel* media_channel_ = nullptr;
209 rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamTrackInterface> track_;
210
211 rtc::scoped_refptr<DtlsTransportInterface> dtls_transport_;
212 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameEncryptorInterface> frame_encryptor_;
213 // |last_transaction_id_| is used to verify that |SetParameters| is receiving
214 // the parameters object that was last returned from |GetParameters|.
215 // As such, it is used for internal verification and is not observable by the
216 // the client. It is marked as mutable to enable |GetParameters| to be a
217 // const method.
218 mutable absl::optional<std::string> last_transaction_id_;
219 std::vector<std::string> disabled_rids_;
220
221 SetStreamsObserver* set_streams_observer_ = nullptr;
222
223 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer_;
224};
225
226// LocalAudioSinkAdapter receives data callback as a sink to the local
227// AudioTrack, and passes the data to the sink of AudioSource.
228class LocalAudioSinkAdapter : public AudioTrackSinkInterface,
229 public cricket::AudioSource {
230 public:
231 LocalAudioSinkAdapter();
232 virtual ~LocalAudioSinkAdapter();
233
234 private:
235 // AudioSinkInterface implementation.
236 void OnData(const void* audio_data,
237 int bits_per_sample,
238 int sample_rate,
239 size_t number_of_channels,
240 size_t number_of_frames,
241 absl::optional<int64_t> absolute_capture_timestamp_ms) override;
242
243 // AudioSinkInterface implementation.
244 void OnData(const void* audio_data,
245 int bits_per_sample,
246 int sample_rate,
247 size_t number_of_channels,
248 size_t number_of_frames) override {
249 OnData(audio_data, bits_per_sample, sample_rate, number_of_channels,
250 number_of_frames,
251 /*absolute_capture_timestamp_ms=*/absl::nullopt);
252 }
253
254 // AudioSinkInterface implementation.
255 int NumPreferredChannels() const override { return num_preferred_channels_; }
256
257 // cricket::AudioSource implementation.
258 void SetSink(cricket::AudioSource::Sink* sink) override;
259
260 cricket::AudioSource::Sink* sink_;
261 // Critical section protecting |sink_|.
262 Mutex lock_;
263 int num_preferred_channels_ = -1;
264};
265
266class AudioRtpSender : public DtmfProviderInterface, public RtpSenderBase {
267 public:
268 // Construct an RtpSender for audio with the given sender ID.
269 // The sender is initialized with no track to send and no associated streams.
270 // StatsCollector provided so that Add/RemoveLocalAudioTrack can be called
271 // at the appropriate times.
272 // If |set_streams_observer| is not null, it is invoked when SetStreams()
273 // is called. |set_streams_observer| is not owned by this object. If not
274 // null, it must be valid at least until this sender becomes stopped.
275 static rtc::scoped_refptr<AudioRtpSender> Create(
276 rtc::Thread* worker_thread,
277 const std::string& id,
278 StatsCollectorInterface* stats,
279 SetStreamsObserver* set_streams_observer);
280 virtual ~AudioRtpSender();
281
282 // DtmfSenderProvider implementation.
283 bool CanInsertDtmf() override;
284 bool InsertDtmf(int code, int duration) override;
285 sigslot::signal0<>* GetOnDestroyedSignal() override;
286
287 // ObserverInterface implementation.
288 void OnChanged() override;
289
290 cricket::MediaType media_type() const override {
291 return cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO;
292 }
293 std::string track_kind() const override {
294 return MediaStreamTrackInterface::kAudioKind;
295 }
296
297 rtc::scoped_refptr<DtmfSenderInterface> GetDtmfSender() const override;
298
299 protected:
300 AudioRtpSender(rtc::Thread* worker_thread,
301 const std::string& id,
302 StatsCollectorInterface* stats,
303 SetStreamsObserver* set_streams_observer);
304
305 void SetSend() override;
306 void ClearSend() override;
307
308 // Hooks to allow custom logic when tracks are attached and detached.
309 void AttachTrack() override;
310 void DetachTrack() override;
311 void AddTrackToStats() override;
312 void RemoveTrackFromStats() override;
313
314 private:
315 cricket::VoiceMediaChannel* voice_media_channel() {
316 return static_cast<cricket::VoiceMediaChannel*>(media_channel_);
317 }
318 rtc::scoped_refptr<AudioTrackInterface> audio_track() const {
319 return rtc::scoped_refptr<AudioTrackInterface>(
320 static_cast<AudioTrackInterface*>(track_.get()));
321 }
322 sigslot::signal0<> SignalDestroyed;
323
324 StatsCollectorInterface* stats_ = nullptr;
325 rtc::scoped_refptr<DtmfSenderInterface> dtmf_sender_proxy_;
326 bool cached_track_enabled_ = false;
327
328 // Used to pass the data callback from the |track_| to the other end of
329 // cricket::AudioSource.
330 std::unique_ptr<LocalAudioSinkAdapter> sink_adapter_;
331};
332
333class VideoRtpSender : public RtpSenderBase {
334 public:
335 // Construct an RtpSender for video with the given sender ID.
336 // The sender is initialized with no track to send and no associated streams.
337 // If |set_streams_observer| is not null, it is invoked when SetStreams()
338 // is called. |set_streams_observer| is not owned by this object. If not
339 // null, it must be valid at least until this sender becomes stopped.
340 static rtc::scoped_refptr<VideoRtpSender> Create(
341 rtc::Thread* worker_thread,
342 const std::string& id,
343 SetStreamsObserver* set_streams_observer);
344 virtual ~VideoRtpSender();
345
346 // ObserverInterface implementation
347 void OnChanged() override;
348
349 cricket::MediaType media_type() const override {
350 return cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO;
351 }
352 std::string track_kind() const override {
353 return MediaStreamTrackInterface::kVideoKind;
354 }
355
356 rtc::scoped_refptr<DtmfSenderInterface> GetDtmfSender() const override;
357
358 protected:
359 VideoRtpSender(rtc::Thread* worker_thread,
360 const std::string& id,
361 SetStreamsObserver* set_streams_observer);
362
363 void SetSend() override;
364 void ClearSend() override;
365
366 // Hook to allow custom logic when tracks are attached.
367 void AttachTrack() override;
368
369#if defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
370 void GenerateKeyFrame() override;
371#endif
372
373 private:
374 cricket::VideoMediaChannel* video_media_channel() {
375 return static_cast<cricket::VideoMediaChannel*>(media_channel_);
376 }
377 rtc::scoped_refptr<VideoTrackInterface> video_track() const {
378 return rtc::scoped_refptr<VideoTrackInterface>(
379 static_cast<VideoTrackInterface*>(track_.get()));
380 }
381
382 VideoTrackInterface::ContentHint cached_track_content_hint_ =
383 VideoTrackInterface::ContentHint::kNone;
384};
